Package: galamm
Title: Generalized Additive Latent and Mixed Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Øystein",
           family = "Sørensen",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "oystein.sorensen@psykologi.uio.no",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0724-3542"))
Description: Estimates generalized additive latent and
    mixed models using maximum marginal likelihood, 
    as defined in Sorensen et al. (2023) 
    <doi:https://doi.org/10.1007/s11336-023-09910-z>. Factor analysis and 
    item response models in which the responses depend 
    nonlinearly on observed predictors can be estimated, 
    with crossed or nested random effects structures defined
    using 'lme4' syntax. Provides efficient computation using
    sparse matrix methods, automatic differentiation, and 
    the Laplace approximation.
